<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="451" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Records of the State–War–Navy Coordinating
                            Committee, Lot 52–M45, 091 Korea: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">General of the Army <persName type="from">Douglas
                                    MacArthur</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Joint Chiefs of
                                    Staff</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-30">30 December 1945</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>CA 56514. Following recommendation has been received from <gloss target="#t_ComGenUSAFIK1">ComGen USAFIK</gloss>:<note n="2" xml:id="d451fn1">Lt. Gen. John R. Hodge.</note>
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“There is great pressure here to send Korean delegation to <gloss target="#t_UNO1">UNO</gloss> convention in January with
                                    expenses paid by Koreans. Believe advantage in lift of morale of
                                    Korean people would justify the authorization and warrant use of
                                    air transport.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>As the subject matter exceeds my authority, request instructions upon
                            which I can base a reply.</p>
                        <closer>[<signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacArthur</hi></signed>]</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>